The paper deals with Convolutional Neural Networks (ConvNets) and their adaptation for efficient representation learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves iterative operations of filter-wise pruning and network optimization, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of activation statistics and priority evaluation, which are techniques commonly used in neural networks and optimization. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image classification, which is a common application of multimedia (cs.MM) research.
